    "summary": "I am an international consultant/advisor and Senior programme manager with an educational background and experience in agricultural economy and social sciences. My extensive experience is grounded in human security and action-oriented research in which I demonstrate a deep understanding and practices of the articulation between development, security and justice as well as the interaction between local and global socio-economic challenge. I have unique skills to facilitate multi-actors dialogue for sustainable conflict transformation and conflicts sensitivity over resource use. While aiming for a holistic and inclusive approach, my focus is on people\u2019s livelihoods improvement in highly dynamic local, regional and global contexts where people need to develop the structures and systems to function best in secure environment.  \n\nAreas of expertise: Human security, Pastoralist livelihoods analysis / improvement; Sustainable Agriculture / Pastoralism value chain development and food security, Process/Result-oriented program formulation, monitoring and evaluation; Partnership development and resource mobilization; Action-oriented research and Capacity building; Development and security nexus; Conflicts sensitivity approach.",
